    <div align="left">
	<hr align="left" width="100%" />

    <!-- message -->
    <div align="left" id="post_message_444093">I got to run through a 4th ed game over the weekend as well as picking up my core books and the first of the 4th ed modules.  I must say that it left me feeling a little underwhelmed.  We were playing pre generated characters that game with the Games Day module.  I'll admit that some of the problems I had were to do with poor GM'ing.  But things like At Will powers that let me cause psychic damage and action points which allowed me to have an extra attack, move or minor action just made things seem a little to easy.<br />
 <br />
When I was reading through the PHB, it seemed as if they were trying to make things stock standard.  The descriptions of races and thier bonuses and suggested classes feels a little like railroading.  By default, the first character I make with any new edition is a half elf male rogue.  I just didn't the feel &quot;it&quot; once I was done.  <br />
 <br />
Maybe if I manage to convince some folks to play regularly and I get more exposure to the rulesets, it will grow on me.  At this stage though, it seems as though they have tried to make things as uniform as possible to make it easier to deliver the online components.</div>
    <!-- / message -->
    
    
