    <div align="left">
	<hr align="left" width="100%" />

    <!-- message -->
    <div align="left" id="post_message_447893">Been playing.<br />
<br />
Have some Pros and Cons.  But basically it boils down to &quot;4th Ed D&amp;D is WoW the Pen and Paper game&quot;.<br />
<br />
Pros<br />
<br />
1.  LOVE how melee classes, have powers now.  Basically, the entire game follows the Book of the Nine Swords(probably my favorite rulebook from 3.5) model now.  It makes being a melee class actually interesting.<br />
<br />
2.  Conversely, casters use pretty much the exact same system.  Which is good that the whole &quot;memorizing, spells per day&quot; system that I never liked was finally done away with after all these years.  The downside to that is real caster classes, like Wizard and Cleric are pretty limited in their spells now, they both play like Sorcerers in 3.5 did.<br />
<br />
3.  I like that saves are all defenses now, and that every attack/spell etc. requires an attack roll, and your old saves are just like your AC against different spells.  It's just a much smoother system.<br />
<br />
4.  I kinda like the new system they have for Monsters as PCs.  On the one hand, a PC monster is no where near as powerful as that same monster as an NPC(until you take into account your class levels).  But at least it doesn't saddle players with level adjustments and useless &quot;monster levels&quot;.<br />
<br />
5.  No more rolling for stats and for your hp each level.  About damn time.  Nothing sucks like having a shitty character forever because of a single bad roll.<br />
<br />
Cons<br />
<br />
1.  Seriously, Healing Surges can go straight to hell.  The fact that any character can go from being totally dying to full hp 30 seconds after a fight ends with no magic at all is just ridiculous.  <br />
<br />
2.  Skills are just oversimplified.  You either have a skill or you don't, and the only difference is 5 points on your rolls?  Harumph.<br />
<br />
3.  I miss the old multiclassing system.  I miss prestige classes.  And I miss templates.<br />
<br />
I'll probably edit this as I think of more things.</div>
    <!-- / message -->
    
    
