    <div align="left">
	<hr align="left" width="100%" />

    <!-- message -->
    <div align="left" id="post_message_452785">For me there are still too much rules.<br />
Especially the powers wich do mostly the same thing for a class. The could have just made a linear damage scale and add a special effect per class. There is nearly no Variation in powers as you level up.<br />
<br />
Also the Warlocks arent really Strikers from their damageoutput. Fey Pact does a little damage, and controls a target. Even the infernal ones are lacking in Damage against a Ranger in my Opinion. <br />
<br />
Then they are very restrictive with skills. Its the choice of wich skill of your class skillset to leave out.<br />
<br />
Whats good is, that combat plays like a tabletop, and Monsters have Powers, no PC can ever have. Racial Ablities to shift, shoot on the run and such.  <br />
But the System isnt made for 1Vs1 type Duels. <br />
<br />
I dont see me designing Encounters for this. so i will play some bought modules with Dungeons, till we have enough Dungeon crawling. ;)</div>
    <!-- / message -->
    
    
